{"TopicId":204060,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"The Analysis of Sea Levels.","CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-15T00:12:07Z","PageNum":41,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"K^2","CreatedById":57710,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-17T17:07:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224398551\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221718372678\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/14/2024 at 6:44 AM, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a theory that the reason big oil is so prominently \u0022green\u0022 is that they see future profits being much larger if the convert petroleum into plastics instead of fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe important part is locking the carbon. We have ways of doing that with old plastics much better than vehicle exhaust. Also, with gasoline and natural gas demand down, these companies would have to build facilities to convert light fractions into plastics as well. That opens a door to eventually replacing crude with captured carbon, making plastics production carbon-negative. It\u0027s a long road to that, but non-fossil power production and electrification of our energy consumption is still a good first step.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-17T17:12:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRe-imagining Forests (Germany)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/c9UprJXSVSg?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Why Europe and America\u2019s dying forests could be good news\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTLDR: decisions made after WWII resulted in monoculture forestry - which has become susceptible to drought and infestation.\u00A0 Massive die-off of trees resulted.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNewer techniques, mixing up the forests is happening.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"farmerben","CreatedById":190194,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-21T02:26:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpruce is good for seaplanes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-21T04:18:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224399356\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221718644333\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/17/2024 at 8:12 PM, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTLDR: decisions made after WWII resulted in monoculture forestry - which has become susceptible to drought and infestation.\u00A0 Massive die-off of trees resulted.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Siberian taiga (the largest biome on the Earth, and the main mechanism of the air decarbonization) mostly consists of larch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt lacks the undergrowth, and its grass is uniform.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n***\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like somebody\u0027s argumenting the wood cutting for windmill building.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Europe needs its native pigwoods with acorns and plowing boars.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-06-21T04:20:57Z\u0022 title=\u002206/21/2024 04:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jun 21\u0022\u003EJune 21\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"boriz","CreatedById":219053,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-21T08:03:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224400164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221718936787\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022farmerben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, farmerben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpruce is good for seaplanes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Spruce Goose was made of Birch. \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hughes_H-4_Hercules\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hughes_H-4_Hercules\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-21T12:32:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224400178\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221718943514\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSiberian taiga (the largest biome on the Earth, and the main mechanism of the air decarbonization) mostly consists of larch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLarch apparently protecting the ice and preventing incursion from other trees\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://phys.org/news/2016-06-siberian-larch-forests-linked-ice.html#google_vignette\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://phys.org/news/2016-06-siberian-larch-forests-linked-ice.html#google_vignette\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr, if you read a different article, maybe not\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://phys.org/news/2011-03-russian-boreal-forests-vegetation.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://phys.org/news/2011-03-russian-boreal-forests-vegetation.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr maybe it is\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://phys.org/news/2007-09-peat-forests-permafrost.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://phys.org/news/2007-09-peat-forests-permafrost.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPanik?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(btw - if you do lose the Larch, we\u0027ll have to rename the Taiga to \u0022Dark Forest\u0022 as the undergrowth will be much denser)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"farmerben","CreatedById":190194,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-25T13:49:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/ZTC85GStU88?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022World\u0027s Most Interesting Places: Vol. 4 | 60 Minutes Full Episodes\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHolistic grazing management could help save the permafrost.\u00A0 \u00A0Snow is an insulating layer that prevents permafrost from forming in the winter.\u00A0 With trees removed and snow trampled more permafrost will grow.\u00A0 Grassland can sequester carbon in soil much faster than forests.\u00A0 Bring back the mammoth!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-25T15:08:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224401473\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221719323344\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022farmerben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, farmerben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBring back the mammoth!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, look, another publicity run by the Pleistocene Park. Check the date on this one:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed704539787\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/180286-meanwhile-in-russia-fighting-climate-change-with-mammoths/?do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3498242\u0026amp;embedComment=3498242\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3498242\u0022 style=\u0022height:294px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-26T03:58:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224401473\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221719323344\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022farmerben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, farmerben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGrassland can sequester carbon in soil much faster than forests.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo the depth of several centimeters, to return back next year.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile the cold swamp forests bury the carbon under several meters of cold water, preventing it from rotting and returning to the air as CH4 and CO2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224401473\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221719323344\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022farmerben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, farmerben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBring back the mammoth!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd herd them at the mammoth milk farm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"boriz","CreatedById":219053,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-26T08:12:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.kew.org/plants/giant-waterlily\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Egiant waterlilly\u003C/a\u003E farms?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey grow ridiculously quickly, up to two meters in seven days, and grow up to three meters in diameter. That\u0027s efficient carbon capture. They could be harvested, say. every two or three weeks and processed into carbon neutral biofuel. And wherever they are farmed, the albedo will be higher, reflecting more of the sun\u0027s radiant energy back out to space.\u00A0 The bigger the farm, the better the impact. Win-win.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022220704132731-03-giant-waterlily.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.63\u0022 height=\u0022533\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.cnn.com/api/v1/images/stellar/prod/220704132731-03-giant-waterlily.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-27T13:07:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust can\u0027t stop imagining the mutant frog that might need a Lilly Pad that big...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-27T15:57:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sddefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ySZGZAvU7uA/sddefault.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-28T04:51:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224402084\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221719503857\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ySZGZAvU7uA/sddefault.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sddefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ySZGZAvU7uA/sddefault.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is just...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot right.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was a Dinosaur show from about 10 years ago - one of the segments had these giant frogs That used to live back then - big enough to eat a small Dino in one bite.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIIRC - one scene had a brontosaurus step on the frog\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anyone remembers this - it\u0027s worth a look.\u00A0 Kinda horrible - but worth it\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-28T05:05:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Offtopic)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe picture above is also a nice allusion to another sci-fi, the \u003Cem\u003EEmancipator\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.fantasticfiction.com/a/ray-aldridge/emancipator/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eseries by Ray Aldridge\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe creature is basically a modified axolotl,\u003Cbr\u003E\nand the main hero\u0027s power armor from the series was named (back-translating from Russian) \u003Cem\u003EIntertribal Light Axolotl Mk. IV\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, for the \u003Cem\u003EEmancipator\u003C/em\u003E reader the scene from \u003Cem\u003EFallout\u003C/em\u003E looks like axolotl meets axolotl.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}